{"editorCode":";  A procedure that always creates a square\n\n;John wrote the procedure \"square\" to construct a square on the scene. He run the procedure giving the value 100 for the variable :x and the value 90 to the the variable :y. After he run it he realised that if he changed the sliders the square appeared broken.  \n\n;Can you fix John's procedure so that it draws a square for any value of :x and :y ?\n\n;Click the papyrus on the left to read the activity istructions.\n;-------------------------------------------\nto square :x :y\nfd :x\nrt 90\nfd 100\nrt :y\nfd 100\nrt 90 \nfd 100\nrt 90\nend\ncs\nsquare 100 90\n\n","hiddenCode":[],"sceneCode":"","cameraPos":{"x":0,"y":1.2246467991473532e-14,"z":200},"character":"Bird","notes":" Instructions\n-----------\n\na) Define and execute the procedure square to see what the bird draws. \n\nTo define the procedure, select the lines from the word \"TO\" to the word \"END\" and then press the \"Insert\" button on your keyboard or the \"Run Code\" (Play) button on the right top of the editor. \n\nTo run the procedure, click on the line \"square 100 90\" and then press the \"Insert\" button on your keyboard or the \"Run Code\" (Play) button on the right top of the editor. \n\nClick on the bird's trace to enable the sliders tool.\nYou can change move the sliders to change the values of the parameters. \n\nb) Fix the procedure so that the bird draws a square for any value of :x and :y. \nYou can add or remove variables. ","sliders":{},"objects":[]}